---
description: Prefer React Server Components; isolate client-only UI in *.client.tsx islands with clear naming
globs: src/**/*.{ts,tsx}
alwaysApply: true
---

Server-first UI and client islands

Default: server

Implement new UI as Server Components whenever possible: data fetching, getTranslations / next-intl server APIs, static structure, and anything that does not require browser-only APIs (useState, useEffect, usePathname, event handlers, window, etc.).
Push work to the server (layouts, page.tsx, server features) and pass plain props (strings, numbers, validated data) into small client pieces.

When you need the client

Add "use client" only where necessary—typically for interactivity, subscriptions (router, media queries, auth session client hooks), or third-party widgets that require the DOM.
Do not mark a large route or shell as client just to use one hook; split instead (see naming below).

Client island naming

Name client-only modules with a.client.tsx suffix (or.client.ts for client-only hooks/utils that use browser APIs), e.g. navbar-actions-rail.client.tsx, hero-scroll-controls.client.tsx.
Keep the default / entry filename without.client for the Server Component that composes islands (e.g. navbar.tsx imports./navbar-actions-rail.client).
One main React component per.client.tsx file still applies (see react-one-component-per-file).

Composition pattern

Server parent owns copy, layout structure, and serializable props; it imports.client.tsx islands for the interactive slices.
Pass Server Components as children (or slots) into client wrappers when a client shell only needs to supply layout chrome or providers—children stay on the server where possible.

Shared logic

Pure helpers (path parsing, class names, formatting) live in *.utils.ts next to the cluster or under feature utils/—import from both server and client without "use client".

Mental model

Prefer server - Prefer.client.tsx island
async server components, getTranslations, serialized props - useState, effects, handlers, Radix/shadcn that need client
Markup that does not depend on browser - usePathname, useRouter, useSession (client), useMediaQuery / useIsMobile
Stable layout and static chrome - Theme toggle, dropdowns, sheets, notifications

See also: react-features-architecture (thin app/, feature ownership), react-one-component-per-file.
